  </section>

  <section id="Section518545" role="openmfg">
      <title>Scheduling</title>

      <para id="Para518546">Planned Orders are a scheduling mechanism used by
    the two planning systems--Master Production Scheduling (MPS) and Material
    Requirements Planning (MRP)--to create "soft" demands for materials and
    capacity required to meet the Production Plan. These Planned Orders are
    converted to actual Work Orders or Purchase Orders as their Lead Time
    approaches.</para>

